<grammar>
<section>
<title>&lt;i&gt;be: I, you, he, she, it&lt;/i&gt; questions</title>
<sectiontitle> We use &lt;i&gt;Am I ...?&lt;/i&gt; and&lt;i&gt; Are you ...?&lt;/i&gt; for questions.</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>sta_gram2_2_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1> I am a doctor.  </text1>
<text1a>&lt;b&gt;Am I&lt;/b&gt; a doctor?</text1a>
<sound1>sta_gram2_2_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2>You are French.  </text2>
<text2a>&lt;b&gt; Are you&lt;/b&gt; French?     </text2a>
<sound2>sta_gram2_2_3.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>We also use &lt;i&gt;Is he/she/it ...?&lt;/i&gt;  </sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>sta_gram2_2_4.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3> He is married.  </text3>
<text3a>&lt;b&gt;Is he&lt;/b&gt; married? </text3a>
<sound3>sta_gram2_2_5.mp3</sound3>
<text4> It's a dog.  </text4>
<text4a>&lt;b&gt;Is it&lt;/b&gt; a dog?</text4a>
<sound4>sta_gram2_2_6.mp3</sound4>
</section>
<section>
<title>&lt;i&gt;be: I, you, he, she, it&lt;/i&gt; questions</title>
